AU  - Addoum, Jawad M
AU  - Kumar, Alok
AU  - Le, Nhan
AU  - Niessen-Ruenzi, Alexandra
T1  - Local Bankruptcy and Geographic Contagion in the Bank Loan Market*
PY  - 2020
Y1  - 2020/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfz023
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 24
IS  - 5
SP  - 997
EP  - 1037
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - We examine whether corporate bankruptcies influence bank loan characteristics of geographically proximate firms. Controlling for industry contagion and local economic conditions, firms headquartered near a bankruptcy event experience a 7 basis point increase in loan spreads. The effect is transitory and cannot be fully explained by local correlated information or lenders’ financial health. Instead, the effect is more pronounced for informationally opaque bankruptcies and borrowers, and weakened among loans with relationship lenders and lenders with significant local presence.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfz023
ER  - 



