TY  - JOUR
AU  - Deuskar, Prachi
AU  - Kumar, Nitin
AU  - Poland, Jeramia Allan
T1  - Signal on the Margin: Behavior of Levered Investors and Future Economic Conditions*
PY  - 2020
Y1  - 2020/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfaa006
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 24
IS  - 5
SP  - 1039
EP  - 1077
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Margin capacity, defined as the aggregate excess debt capacity of investors buying securities on margin, strongly predicts (i) lower S&amp;P 500 returns, (ii) lower growth in aggregate earnings, dividends, employment, and overall economic activity, (iii) higher macro, financial, and policy uncertainty, (iv) lower interest rates, (v) tighter lending standards by banks, and (vi) lower intermediary equity capital. High margin capacity is a precursor, not a response, to borrowing and intermediary constraints and higher volatility. It typically arises when levered investors with profitable past positions limit their leverage. We interpret that it reflects informed investors’ conservatism ahead of bad times.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfaa006
ER  - 



